  "key_theorem": "The EML Musical Asymmetry Theorem: Musical timbre qualities map to EML strata: brightness = EML-2 (log centroid), inharmonicity = EML-2, beating = EML-3. Emotional peaks (frisson/chills) = EML-\u221e \u2192 EML-3 depth collapses: buildup = EML-1 (exponential approach), surprise = EML-\u221e, resolution = EML-3. The Asymmetry Theorem generates composition rules: tension uses exp-spaced intervals (EML-1); release uses log-compressed intervals (EML-2). Rhythm: isochrony = EML-0, syncopation = EML-3, surprise/missing beat = EML-\u221e. Musical structure follows the EML depth ladder: 0 (counting) \u2192 1 (exponential tension) \u2192 2 (log geometry) \u2192 3 (oscillation) \u2192 \u221e (feeling).",
